1
00:00:05,118 --> 00:00:09,060
How we observe things,
and the impressions that enter within us;

2
00:00:09,060 --> 00:00:12,945
and how we consider them
and interpret them as reality;

3
00:00:13,242 --> 00:00:15,551
and whether it’s based 
upon ultimate reality

4
00:00:15,551 --> 00:00:18,735
or temporal manifestations 
of what appears to be real.

5
00:00:18,890 --> 00:00:22,423
[Victory Through Surrender]

6
00:00:22,962 --> 00:00:24,673
So that’s why it says 
in the Bhāgavatam,

7
00:00:24,673 --> 00:00:28,422
“Whatever you see, whether it’s real 
or it appears to be real,

8
00:00:28,422 --> 00:00:31,625
it’s all indirectly from Me.”

9
00:00:31,625 --> 00:00:34,269
Like Guru Mahārāj said,
“The supreme hypnotist.”

10
00:00:34,269 --> 00:00:39,737
As He compels you to see, 
you have to see that; you will see that.

11
00:00:40,082 --> 00:00:43,480
And unless He withdraws that, 
then you won’t see it otherwise;

12
00:00:43,529 --> 00:00:47,074
“Daivī hy eṣā guṇa-mayī 
mama māyā duratyayā” (Bg: 7.14).

13
00:00:47,089 --> 00:00:52,831
Like Mayā. We’re so afraid of Mayā,
and that’s good.

14
00:00:53,269 --> 00:00:57,331
But, where … Guru Mahārāj meant 
that Mayā’s not afraid of any jīva,

15
00:00:57,533 --> 00:00:59,925
but she’s afraid of Kṛṣṇa.

16
00:01:00,357 --> 00:01:06,160
Sometimes we hear, 
she’s shy to come before Kṛṣṇa,

17
00:01:06,191 --> 00:01:11,791
but, “Mām eva ye prapadyante 
Māyām etāṁ taranti te” (Bg: 7.14):

18
00:01:11,791 --> 00:01:13,379
“Surrendering to Me,

19
00:01:13,379 --> 00:01:17,391
then you can cross beyond her influence; 
it can be withdrawn.”

